-- Montenegro Talks to Poly, Bechtel to Build Roads, Poslovni Says
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2013-01-04T08:23:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-04/montenegro-talks-to-poly-bechtel-to-build-roads-poslovni-says.html
Montenegro is in talks with China’s
 Poly Group (600048) , Bechtel Group Inc., a U.S. construction and
development firm, and the  European Investment Bank  to build a
highway through the Balkan country,  Poslovni Dnevnik  reported on
its website, citing Transport Minister Ivan Brajovic.  The building of the 170-kilometer (105-mile) highway from
Bar on Montenegro’s Adriatic coast to Boljari, on the border
with  Serbia , could start in the second half of the year,
Brajovic said, according to the Zagreb-based business newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic at 
